	   <tr><td colspan=2>100% haste would cut the delay of a weapon in half. 100% haste means 100% faster attacks, which is twice as many...so the 28dly weapon becomes a 14dly weapon.<br><br>Formula for figuring new delay of weapon after haste.<br><br>(60 / (( 60 / ((dly / 10) x 1.xx ))) x 10 = new dly.<br><br>XX is the haste percentage in decimal. so if 50% haste you'd multiply by 1.5 if 100% by 2.<br><br>Nathus L'Antryl<br>57 DE SK<br>Crimson Watchers<br>Mithaniel Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
