<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99584845681169></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99584845681169><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2197&mid=99584845681169>Haste vs. Caster Stats</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2197&mid=99584845681169#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=44631><span id=Sage>AzathothStrongbear</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>26 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jul 22nd 8:34 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You can get WIS, INT, and mana in a lot of different slots, a lot of different ways.  You can have many items in may slots with WIS/INT/Mana and they will all add together.  However, you can only have 1 haste item contribute towards your overall haste.  For that reason, haste is more valuable than wisdom, int, or mana.  You can have two 6 wis ring to make up for not having this cloak.  You cannot have two 13% haste items to make up for the haste on this cloak, because two 13% haste items only give you 13% haste, not 26%.  That is why haste is always more important than any other stat on any item, and it is why haste items go to melees first.<br>&nbsp;<br>Azathoth Strongbear <br>58 Human Warrior<br>&lt;Shadowhunters&gt; E`Ci</td></tr>
